    "description": "The FEA modeling framework must demonstrate that predicted compression-bending QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) agree with experimental measurements within pre-established acceptance bounds: relative difference less than 10% and E/uval less than 1.96. This requirement is derived from 21 CFR 820.30(f) and the FDA guidance document 'Reporting of Computational Modeling Studies in Medical Device Submissions' (2016).",
    "source": "https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-21/chapter-I/subchapter-H/part-820/subpart-C/section-820.30"
  },
